Rating: 3
I officially totally screwed with this recipe on the first time out. First of all, I NEVER cook with boneless, skinless unless it's going on a shish kabob. There's no flavor whatsoever to impart but whatever whoever packaged them injected it with so that was right out. What I did do was this: I made a whole roasted chicken stuffed with meyer lemon halves, 4-5 smashed garlic cloves, rosemary, thyme, sage, and several small golden pearl onions. I squeezed the juice of one meyer lemon and one naval orange over the top as well as a little bit of salt, some fresh ground pink peppercorns and fresh ground telecherry pepper. I started the oven at 500 for 15 in a glass baking dish to collect juices, then 450 for 15, then 425 for 30 and let stand for 20. Once I'd collected about a cup of juices I started the sauce. I transferred the juices to a small sauce pan and brought it and the capers (left out the olives due to a sig other distaste) to a boil, added a cup of vegetable stock and then boiled until it was just a bubbling quarter inch of liquid, then I deglazed the pan with some pinot grigio.

