Made this for a crowd at New Year's and it was excellent. I baked it in the oven (easier when you have guests I think). Here's what I did: Used skinless chicken thighs, instead of roasting the lemons, I juiced half the lemons and sliced half the lemons, and used half the butter. For the chicken, I browned the chicken on the stove in a pan, but then put the chicken, olives, and capers in a baking dish. Delazed the saute pan with the chicken broth and then added it to the pan. Baked the whole dish at 350 for 50 minutes (actually longer since people werenn't ready to eat.) Put chicken on a platter and put the pan on top of the stove to simmer. Added lemon juice, butter, parsley. Simmered until butter melted and sauce thickened a bit (3 min?). Poured the sauce over the chicken, garish with the lemon slices.

