Rating: 3
This dish works exactly as it should as long as one keeps in mind the need to control the salt of the capers and the fat in the oil and butter. Use salt-preserved capers and reconstitute them by soaking them in water and then draining them. Reduce the amount of fat by using 4T oil and only 2T butter...the sauce is still rich. Serve it over steamed fresh spinich...no additional fat. This cooks quickly and can be presented in a lovely server with the bed of spinich already in place. Great for a hot buffet! And if the chicken breasts are large they can be cut in half because this dish is very satisfying!

