Rating: 2
This was a nice dinner, but won't be added to my repertoire. The chicken was very tender, but the sauce just wasn't as good as similar ones I've made. The only changes I made were to soak my olives for an hour beforehand (the ones I bought were desperately salty!), and I reduced the butter at the end to 2 TBSP. I served the chicken on a bed of steamed spinach, with some ravioli medallions around the edge of the plate. The lemon slices looked great, and definitely added flavour to the sauce, but we treated them as a garnish, and didn't eat them - I'm wondering if the people who found them bitter did? I may steal the roasted lemon idea to use in another recipe . . .!

